## Installation

Via `pip` command:

```bash
pip install {{ project_name }}
```

...or you can clone the repo and install it using `pip` too:

```bash
git clone git://github.com/{{ github_username }}/{{ project_name }}.git
cd {{ project_name }}
pip install -e .
```

Then add `{{ module_name }}` to your `settings.py`:

```python
INSTALLED_APPS = (
    # ...
    "{{ module_name }}",
)
```

Then run the migrations:

```bash
python manage.py migrate
```

