## Initial Setup

This project was generated using [django-app-starter](https://github.com/matagus/django-app-starter).
A few one-time steps are needed to fully activate the included GitHub Actions workflows:

- [ ] **GitHub Pages** — Enable GitHub Pages in repo Settings to publish your docs site
- [ ] **Codecov** — Add a `CODECOV_TOKEN` secret to your repo for coverage reporting
- [ ] **PyPI Publishing** — Create a `release` environment and add `PYPI_API_TOKEN` secret for automated PyPI uploads

See the [Post-Generation Setup Guide](https://matagus.github.io/django-app-starter/setup/) for step-by-step instructions.

## Releasing a New Version

1. Tag a commit: `git tag v0.1.0`
2. Push the tag: `git push origin v0.1.0`
3. A draft release is automatically created in the **Releases** tab
4. Edit the draft, review the release notes, and publish it
5. Publishing triggers the workflow that uploads the package to PyPI

See the [Release Process Guide](https://matagus.github.io/django-app-starter/release-process/) for full details.

